<TITLE> Landslide kills 2 in Cox's Bazar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Cox's Bazar, Apr 08 (bdnews24.com)  Two people died in a landslide at Dhalirchara of Ramu upazila in Cox's Bazar at around 9am on Thursday. The landslide occurred as the two were cutting a hill to build their house. They are Shamsul Alam, 30, of Bara Dhalirchara of Rashidnagar Union and Saiful Islam, 27, of Dhalirchara Murapara area. Faridul Alam, Rashidnagar chairman, said that Shamsul Alam, son of Shahab Mia of Bara Dhalirchara, decided to move out of his house after a quarrel with his father. Deciding to build a new house, Shamsul and a hired hand began to cut a hill beside his old house on Thursday morning. All of a sudden the hill crumbled upon them. Both died on the spot. He said that after recovering the two, their bodies were sent to Ramu Upazila Health Complex. But the on duty doctor declared that they had died on their way to the hospital. The chairman said that the bodies would soon be buried, without a post mortem.
